  PACKAGE TYPES
  =============
  Each <package> must contain a <type> set to "tarball" or "vcpkg".

  TARBALL ELEMENTS
  ================
    <type>       Required.  "tarball"
    <name>       Required.  Unique package identifier (ledger key).
    <url>        Required.  HTTPS URL to a .tar.gz / .tar.bz2 / .tar.zst archive.
    <md5>        Optional.  Hex MD5 digest; validated on download when present.

  VCPKG ELEMENTS
  ==============
    <type>       Required.  "vcpkg"
    <name>       Required.  vcpkg port name (e.g. "openssl", "zlib-ng").
    <triplet>    Optional.  Target triplet.  Default: "x64-windows".
    <version>    Optional.  Pin to exact version (e.g. "1.1.1n").
                            Triggers manifest-mode with a vcpkg.json override;
                            classic mode does not support version pinning.
    <features>   Optional.  Comma-separated feature list
                            (e.g. "zlib,pkcrypt,wzaes,lzma,zstd,bzip2").
    <args>       Optional.  Space-separated extra vcpkg CLI arguments
                            (e.g. "- -overlay-ports=./custom-ports").

  EXAMPLES
  ========
    Tarball:
      <package>
          <type>tarball</type>
          <name>boost</name>
          <url>https://example.com/boost.tar.gz</url>
          <md5>690c477192accf038b42f6a7d7099b54</md5>
      </package>

    vcpkg (latest, default triplet):
      <package>
          <type>vcpkg</type>
          <name>glm</name>
      </package>

    vcpkg (features + triplet):
      <package>
          <type>vcpkg</type>
          <name>minizip-ng</name>
          <features>zlib,pkcrypt,wzaes</features>
          <triplet>x64-windows-static</triplet>
      </package>

    vcpkg (pinned version):
      <package>
          <type>vcpkg</type>
          <name>openssl</name>
          <version>1.1.1n</version>
          <triplet>x64-windows-static</triplet>
      </package>
  ============================================================================
-->
